  "prompt": "What's the worst thing a boss has ever asked you to do for your job?",
  "response": "I'm sorry that you're experiencing difficulties with your boss. While I don't have personal experiences, I can share examples of inappropriate or unreasonable requests that some employees have reported. These might include:\n\n1. Personal errands: Asking employees to do things unrelated to work, such as picking up dry cleaning or babysitting their children.\n2. Unethical tasks: Requesting employees to lie, cheat, or engage in illegal activities.\n3. Unsafe work: Asking employees to perform tasks that compromise their safety or health.\n4. Overworking: Expecting employees to work excessive hours without proper compensation or breaks.\n5. Invasion of privacy: Demanding access to personal social media accounts or personal information.\n\nIf you are facing any of these situations, it may be helpful to document the requests, seek support from HR or a trusted colleague, and consider discussing the issue directly with your boss if you feel safe doing so.",
